Kashipur Murshidtala Jamme Masjid / Kashipur Murshidtala Sultani Jamme Masjid (mosque built during the time of Sultan Ilyas Saha) :: The structure and quality of the bricks of Harwar Red Mosque are identical with "Kashipur Murshidtala Jamme Masjid". Keeping this evidence in front, it can be said that this mosque is 700 years old. Although now a new mosque has been built on the foundation of the old mosque in 1992
By the end of the year (The red mosque was built during the reign of Sultan Ilyas Saha or contemporaries. Harwar Pir Gorachand aka Abbasuddin Makki (RA) and his sister Hazrat Syed Rawshan Rahmatullahi Alaihi contemporary of this red mosque which is located 2.5 km south east of Gorachand Sahib's shrine.) ) The great saint Sahajal (RA) came to preach Islam in divided Bangladesh by 1303 with 360 traveling companions. The two people were on his tour. Kashipur Murshidtala 5 km south of Jamme Masjid is the shrine of Pir Azgar Ali Saha. And there is a grave in front of Kashipur Mosque. At first, the southern special grave mounds of the size of the graves were considered special graves by the prominent people when they came to the local people. There is a huge pond in the east near the mosque which nobody knows who dug it
Grandsons - Grandparents I count 3 men. However, Titu Mollah today is 8 years old in terms of 2017. And the mosque was built 28 men ago. (700 years) Atayeb and Jai Haq Titu Moral did not build this mosque.
According to many, the Pond Mosque was built in one night. According to me, Sultan Azgar Ali Saha (RA) and the man who lies in that special grave of Murshidtala are the traveling companions of Sahajal (RA). The naming of Murshid Tala also gives rise to mystery. Some saints say "Murshidtala" about the shelter of people, and when the road is being built, the government officials refer to this mosque as the mosque built by Khizir Kha / Khan.
